#!N  #!Rwindset Customizing the VPE Window #!N #!EC #!N #!N Under 
the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Options #!EF menu bar category are selections for customizing 
the window: #!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Tool Palettes 
#!EF #!I50 #!N Use as a toggle by clicking to close 
the palettes and make the working area on the canvas larger. 
#!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Grid... #!EF #!I50 #!N A dialog box, 
illustrated in  #!Lgridbox72,dxall353 f Figure 72  #!EL  , appears for you to enter new values. 
#!I0 #!N #!N #!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Rgridbox72 #!N #!N Graphics omitted 
from Online Documentation. Please see the manual. #!N Figure 72. Grid 
Dialog Box #!EF #!N #!EC #!N #!N The  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Grid... #!EF 
option allows you to specify whether the tools you place on 
the canvas automatically align on a grid pattern. You can enable 
the grid pattern by clicking on one of the following: #!CForestGreen 
#!N #!N  #!F-adobe-courier-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   #!N 1D Horizontal #!N 1D Vertical #!N 
2D #!EF #!EF #!N #!N #!EC The default is none. #!N 
#!N You can control the spacing of the grid pattern by 
changing the number of vertical and horizontal pixels. Specify how the 
tools are to be aligned on the grid by changing the 
alignment toggle buttons. For example, the dialog box in  #!Lgridbox72,dxall353 f Figure 72  #!EL  specifies 
grid spacing of 50 pixels, with the center of a tool 
being placed at a grid position. #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next 
